============================================================
SYNTHETIC STRESS–DIALOGUE INTERACTION DATASET
============================================================

DATASET SUMMARY
------------------------------------------------------------
This dataset is a synthetic multimodal dataset designed to
mirror the structure of participant data from an interactive
10-minute game session. Around 30 participants are simulated.
The dataset is used for developing and validating clustering
pipelines (e.g., K-Prototypes) that combine physiological,
behavioral, and self-report features.

------------------------------------------------------------
DATASET STRUCTURE
------------------------------------------------------------
Physiological: Electrodermal Activity (EDA)

Behavioral / Categorical: Stress labels, dialogue decisions, tendency based on stress and dialoug options. 

Self-report / Continuous: valence, arousal, agency, identification, immersion, system usability


------------------------------------------------------------
SYNTHETIC DATA GENERATION
------------------------------------------------------------
The dataset is fully synthetic and created to:
• mimic the size and structure of the real target dataset
• approximate realistic statistical patterns
• allow testing of preprocessing and clustering workflows

No real participant data is included!

------------------------------------------------------------
DATASET FEATURES
------------------------------------------------------------

Categorical Features:
• Stressed–Honest
• Stressed–Defensive
• Stressed–Mixed
• Non-stressed–Honest
• Non-stressed–Defensive
• Non-stressed–Mixed
• Mixed–Honest
• Mixed–Defensive
• Mixed–Mixed

These combine:
• Stress pattern across narrative points
• Dialogue tendencies (honest/defensive/mixed)

Continuous Features:
Physiological - EDA 
Self-report(Likert 1–7) - 
• valence
• arousal
• agency
• identification
• immersion
• system questions



------------------------------------------------------------
PREPROCESSING
------------------------------------------------------------
• Inspected for missing values

• Removed irrelevant variables:
  - Participant ID
  - Detailed state logs
  - Detailed choice logs

• Separated categorical and numerical features

• Scaled all numerical variables using min–max normalization

• Used:
  - Euclidean distance for numerical features
  - Hamming distance for categorical features


------------------------------------------------------------
INTENDED USE
------------------------------------------------------------
Intended for:
• developing and validating mixed-feature clustering pipelines
• testing preprocessing workflows


------------------------------------------------------------
LIMITATIONS
------------------------------------------------------------
• Fully synthetic data; not reflective of real human patterns
• Relationships are approximate, not empirically validated
• Results will not generalize to real users


------------------------------------------------------------
ETHICAL CONSIDERATIONS
------------------------------------------------------------
• No personal or identifiable information
• No real participant involvement
• Safe for open sharing and unrestricted development use


------------------------------------------------------------
LICENSING
------------------------------------------------------------
• MIT License


------------------------------------------------------------
FILE DESCRIPTION
------------------------------------------------------------
File name: synthetic_evaluation_data.csv

The file contains all synthetic features used in development of the
clustering pipeline.


